## Quick Decision Matrix

### Badge Style

| Context | Has Buttons in Row? | Badge Style |
|---------|-------------------|-------------|
| Table row | ✅ Yes | `badgeStyle="outlined"` |
| Table row | ❌ No | `badgeStyle="filled"` or default |
| Stat card | N/A | `badgeStyle="filled"` or default |
| Alert banner | N/A | `badgeStyle="filled"` or default |
| Header section | N/A | `badgeStyle="filled"` or default |
| Modal content | Depends | Use filled unless buttons compete visually |

### Badge Sizing

| Context | Next to Title/Heading? | Font Size |
|---------|----------------------|-----------|
| Section header | ✅ Yes | Match title size (e.g., 1.4em) |
| Kanban column header | ✅ Yes | Match column title (e.g., 1.1rem) |
| Card header | ✅ Yes | Match card title (e.g., 1rem) |
| Table cell | ❌ No | Use default badge size (sm/md) |
| Body content | ❌ No | Use default badge size (sm/md) |
| Standalone | N/A | Use default badge size (sm/md) |

## Implementation Checklist

### For Table Badges

When creating or reviewing table components with status indicators:

- [ ] Does the table row contain action buttons?
- [ ] Does the table row contain status badges?
- [ ] If both: Are badges using `badgeStyle="outlined"`?
- [ ] Are helper functions (like `getStatusBadge`) configured to return outlined badges?
- [ ] Do standalone badge contexts (cards, headers) still use filled badges appropriately?

### For Header Badges

When creating or reviewing section headers with badges:

- [ ] Is the badge next to a title/heading?
- [ ] Does the header use a custom font size (not body default)?
- [ ] Is there a CSS rule to match the badge font size to the title?
- [ ] Have you scoped the sizing rule to the specific header context?
- [ ] Do table/body badges still use default sizes?

## Badge Sizing in Headers

### The Pattern

When badges appear alongside titles in section headers, kanban columns, or other header contexts, their font size should match the adjacent text for visual coherence.

### ✅ GOOD - Matched Badge Sizing

```css
/* Kanban column header with title and count badge */
.kanban-column__title {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  font-weight: var(--mds-font-weight-bold);
}

.kanban-column__header .ui-Badge {
  font-size: 1.1rem; /* Matches title */
}
```

```tsx
{/* Section header with title and notification badge */}
<div className="section-header">
  <h3 className="section-title">Recent Projects</h3> {/* 1.4em */}
  <Badge variant="error">3 Updates</Badge> {/* Should also be 1.4em */}
</div>
```

```css
.section-title {
  font-size: 1.4em;
}

.section-header .ui-Badge {
  font-size: 1.4em; /* Matches section title */
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Mismatched Badge Sizing

```css
/* Title is large but badge stays small */
.kanban-column__title {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
}

/* Badge uses default small size - creates visual imbalance */
.kanban-column__header .ui-Badge {
  /* No override - will be 0.75rem from default sm size */
}
```

