### Why This Matters

- **Visual Harmony**: Matching sizes create cohesive, balanced layouts
- **Hierarchy**: Properly sized badges don't compete with or undermine title importance
- **Readability**: Consistent sizing makes headers easier to scan
- **Professional Appearance**: Mismatched sizes look unpolished

### When to Override Badge Size

Override the default badge size when:

1. Badge appears directly next to a title/heading
2. Badge is part of a header component (section, column, card)
3. Badge displays a count or tally related to the header
4. Default badge size (sm/md/lg) doesn't match adjacent text

**Don't override when:**
- Badge is in body content (use default sizes)
- Badge is in a table cell (use default sizes)
- Badge is standalone without adjacent text

